This paper discusses techniques for strengthening CAPTCHAs, which are commonly used to prevent bots from interacting with websites. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computer security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), software engineering (cs.SE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Given the focus on security and anti-bot measures, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also discusses novel techniques for improving the user experience, which could fall under cs.HC or cs.SE.
